article.headline: Albany, N.Y. 71, St. Bonaventure 56
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Jamar Wilson scored 22 points and Jason Siggers added 16 to lead Albany to a 71-56 win over St. Bonaventure Saturday. Albany (5-4) led 27-23 in the opening half, then scored 11 of the next 13 points to end the period with a 38-25 lead. Brian Connelly, who had 10 points, scored before Reid Anderson hit a 3-pointer. Wilson, who also had eight rebounds, seven assists and four steals, ended the run with a 10-footer and a pair of free throws. St. Bonaventure (3-7) closed the gap to seven in the second half when Zarryon Fereti made a pair of free throws to make it 40-33 with 15:11 remaining. But the Great Danes responded with a 10-3 run to pull away. Brent Wilson, who had 12 points and 11 rebounds for Albany, made a 3-pointer during that stretch and a layup by Siggers made it 50-36. St. Bonaventure was held to 32.8 percent shooting from the field. A.J. Hawkins led the Bonnies with 14 points and eight rebounds. Paul Williams and James Williams each added 12 points.
